quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,73,"And when Our verses are recited to them as clear evidences, those who disbelieve say to those who believe, ",1:[In regard to worldly interests.]
  19,74,"And how many a generation have We destroyed before them who were better in possessions and [outward] appearance?"
  19,75,"Say, "
  20,55,"From it [i.e., the earth] We created you, and into it We will return you, and from it We will extract you another time."
  20,56,"And We certainly showed him [i.e., Pharaoh] Our signs - all of them - but he denied and refused."
  20,57,"He said, "
  21,31,"And We placed within the earth firmly set mountains, lest it should shift with them, and We made therein [mountain] passes [as] roads that they might be guided."
  21,32,"And We made the sky a protected ceiling, but they, from its signs,{1} are turning away.",1:[The signs present in the heavens.]
  21,33,"And it is He who created the night and the day and the sun and the moon; all [heavenly bodies] in an orbit are swimming."
  22,7,"And [that they may know] that the Hour is coming - no doubt about it - and that Allāh will resurrect those in the graves."
  22,8,"And of the people is he who disputes about Allāh without knowledge or guidance or an enlightening book [from Him],"
  22,9,"Twisting his neck [in arrogance] to mislead [people] from the way of Allāh. For him in the world is disgrace, and We will make him taste on the Day of Resurrection the punishment of the Burning Fire [while it is said],"